{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17527301","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17527301"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:30:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:30:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14198"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583972","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583972"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:33:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:33:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14198"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14198","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14198"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.87,0.03,0.04,0.04,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6884"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96065"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6884","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6884"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14198"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78797"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"5351"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12734"},{"type":"tags","id":"12737"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"15740"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29685"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96065","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96065"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old Aboriginal man presents to the General Practice clinic for a routine health check. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. During the consultation, he mentions feeling disconnected from his community since moving to the city for work two years ago. He expresses a desire to reconnect with his culture and traditional practices. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a cultural determinant of health that may positively impact this patient\u0027s wellbeing?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Connection to Country and traditional lands","Educational attainment","Access to Western medical services","Socioeconomic status","Genetic predisposition"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECultural determinants of health are factors that strengthen and support the health and wellbeing of Indigenous peoples. These determinants are deeply rooted in Indigenous cultures, traditions, and ways of life. In this scenario, the most relevant cultural determinant of health is \u003Cstrong\u003EConnection to Country and traditional lands\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConnection to Country\u003C/strong\u003E is a fundamental aspect of Indigenous Australian culture and identity. It encompasses a spiritual, physical, and cultural relationship with the land, which is integral to overall health and wellbeing. For many Indigenous Australians, being on Country and participating in traditional practices can provide a sense of belonging, purpose, and cultural continuity, all of which contribute positively to mental, emotional, and physical health.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccess to Western medical services\u003C/strong\u003E, while important for managing health conditions, is not specifically a cultural determinant of health. It falls under the broader category of social determinants of health, which affect all populations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESocioeconomic status\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eeducational attainment\u003C/strong\u003E are social determinants of health that can impact all populations, including Indigenous Australians. However, they are not specific cultural determinants of health for Indigenous peoples.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenetic predisposition\u003C/strong\u003E refers to inherited genetic factors that may influence health outcomes. While genetics can play a role in health, it is not a cultural determinant of health.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther important cultural determinants of health for Indigenous Australians include language, family and kinship, traditional knowledge systems, cultural expression, and self-determination. Healthcare providers should be aware of these factors and incorporate them into their approach to provide culturally safe and effective care for Indigenous patients.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cultural determinants of health are factors that strengthen and support the health and wellbeing of Indigenous peoples.","Connection to Country, cultural beliefs, and traditional knowledge systems are important cultural determinants of health for Indigenous Australians.","Understanding and respecting cultural determinants of health is crucial for providing culturally safe healthcare to Indigenous populations."],"references":["Verbunt E, Luke J, Paradies Y, Bamblett M, Salamone C, Jones A, Kelaher M. Cultural determinants of health for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people\u2013a narrative overview of reviews. International Journal for Equity in Health. 2021 Dec;20:1-9."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78797"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14198"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/78797"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-30T21:01:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-01T14:40:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6884"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96065"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Understand (interpreting and summarizing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"rel